1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper proposes a method to enhance laparoscopic images by removing surgical smoke, which involves image processing techniques commonly used in computer vision.
2. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with enhancing laparoscopic images, which can be considered as a type of multimedia content.
3. cs.GR (Graphics): The paper involves image processing techniques to remove surgical smoke from laparoscopic images, which can be considered as a type of graphics processing.
4. cs.RO (Robotics): Laparoscopic surgery is often performed using robotic systems, and the proposed method can be useful in improving the visibility of the surgical field for the robot.
5. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper uses a variational approach to decompose laparoscopic images into unwanted smoke part and enhanced part, which can be considered as an information-theoretic approach.
